<vcelldoc>
<page title="Predefined Constants and Math Functions">

	
	<introduction>
	The Virtual Cell specifies a set of reserved symbols and constants and a subset of math functions that can be used in expressions and computations.
	</introduction>
	
	<appearance>
		<imgReference target = "ConstsAndMathFns.GIF"/>  
	</appearance>
	
	<operations>
	<para>
	Clicking the 'Parameters and Functions' item in the 'Navigation' panel on the left of a VCell document displays the Parameters and Functions in the 'View' panel on the right. 
	This view has 2 tabs. Clicking on the <bold>Predefined Constants and Math Functions</bold> tab displays a list of the allowed VCell constants and math functions in a table. This table is not editable. 
	The list of symbols, constants and functions are classified as follows: 
	</para>
	
	<para> <bold>Reserved Symbols</bold></para>
	<list>
		<item><bold>t</bold> - time</item>
	    <item><bold>x</bold> - x coord</item>
	    <item><bold>y</bold> - y coord</item>
	    <item><bold>z</bold> - z coord</item>
	</list>
	
	<para> <bold>Reserved Constants</bold></para>
	<list>
	    <item><bold>_T_</bold> - temperature in degree Kelvin</item> 
	    <item><bold>_PI_</bold> - PI constant = 3.1428571428</item>
	    <item><bold>_F_</bold> - Faraday constant = 9.648e4 Coloumb_per_mole</item>
	    <item><bold>_F_nmol_</bold> - Faraday constant = 9.648e-5 Coulomb_per_nano-mole</item>
	    <item><bold>_N_pmol_</bold> - Avagadro Number (scaled) = 6.02e11 molecules_per_pico-mole</item>
	    <item><bold>_K_GHK_</bold> - Goldman-Hodgkin-Katz unit scale = 1e-9</item>
	    <item><bold>_R_</bold> - Gas Constant = 8314.0 mVolts_Coulomb_per_Kelvin_per_mole</item>
	    <item><bold>K_millivolts_per_volt</bold> - voltage scale = 1000</item>
	</list>
    	
	<para> <bold>Math Functions</bold></para>
	<list>
		<item><bold>abs(x)</bold> - absolute value</item>
		<item><bold>acos(x)</bold> - inverse cosine function</item>  
		<item><bold>acosh(x)</bold> - inverse hyperbolic cosine function</item>
		<item><bold>acot(x)</bold> - inverse cotangent function</item>
		<item><bold>acoth(x)</bold> - inverse hyperbolic cotangent function</item>
		<item><bold>acsc(x)</bold> - inverse cosecant function</item>
		<item><bold>acsch(x)</bold> - inverse hyperbolic cosecant function</item>
		<item><bold>asec(x)</bold> - inverse secant</item>
		<item><bold>asech(x)</bold> - inverse hyperbolic secant function</item>
		<item><bold>asin(x)</bold> - inverse since function</item>
		<item><bold>asinh(x)</bold> - inverse hyperbolic sine function</item>
		<item><bold>atan(x)</bold> - inverse tangent function</item>
		<item><bold>atan2(x,y)</bold> - similar to atan(y/x), except places the angle in the correct quadrant</item>
		<item><bold>atanh(x)</bold> - inverse hyperbolic tangent function</item>
		<item><bold>ceil(x)</bold> - smallest integral value not less than x</item>
		<item><bold>cos(x)</bold> - cosine function</item>  
		<item><bold>cosh(x)</bold> - hyperbolic cosine function</item>
		<item><bold>cot(x)</bold> - cotangent function</item>
		<item><bold>coth(x)</bold> - hyperbolic cotangent function</item>
		<item><bold>csc(x)</bold> - cosecant function</item>
		<item><bold>csch(x)</bold> - hyperbolic cosecant function</item>
		<item><bold>exp(x)</bold> - exponential function, e^x</item>     
		<item><bold>factorial(x)</bold> - factorial function  x!</item>
		<item><bold>floor(x)</bold> - largest integral value not greater than x</item>
		<item><bold>log(x)</bold> - natural logarithmic function</item>  
		<item><bold>log10(x)</bold> - base 10 logarithmic function</item>
		<item><bold>max(x,y)</bold> - maximum of x and y</item>  
		<item><bold>min(x,y)</bold> - minimum of x and y</item>  
		<item><bold>pow(x,y)</bold> - power function, x^y</item>
		<item><bold>sec(x)</bold> - secant function</item>
		<item><bold>sech(x)</bold> - hyperbolic secant function</item>
		<item><bold>sin(x)</bold> - sine function</item>
		<item><bold>sinh(x)</bold> - hyperbolic sine function</item>
		<item><bold>sqrt(x)</bold> - square root</item>
		<item><bold>tan(x)</bold> - tagent function</item>  
		<item><bold>tanh(x)</bold> - hyperbolic tangent function</item>
	</list>
	
	<para> <bold>Special </bold> <link target="output_functions">Output Function</link> <bold> Operators</bold></para>
	<list>
		<item><bold>vcGrad(variableName,{'x','y','z','m'})</bold> - Spatial gradient, non-membrane variable name, 'x','y','z' directions or 'm' magnitude. (include single quotes ' ')</item>
	</list>
	</operations>
	
</page>

